# SAML Flask App

A Flask web application with SAML 2.0 Single Sign-On (SSO) authentication.

## Requirements

- Python 3.8+
- xmlsec1 (system dependency)

```bash
# Ubuntu/Debian
sudo apt-get install xmlsec1

# macOS
brew install libxmlsec1
```

## Installation

```bash
git clone <your-repo-url>
cd saml-flask-app

python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate

pip install -r requirements.txt
```

## Configuration

Update `saml/settings.json` with your Identity Provider (IdP) details before running the app.

To generate SP certificates:

```bash
openssl req -x509 -newkey rsa:2048 -keyout saml/certs/sp.key \
  -out saml/certs/sp.crt -days 365 -nodes
```

## Running

```bash
python run.py
```

App runs at `http://localhost:5000`

## Testing

```bash
pytest tests/ -v
```

Tests use `unittest.mock` to simulate SAML authentication without a real IdP.

## Project Structure

```
saml-flask-app/
├── app/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── utils.py
│   └── views.py
├── saml/
│   ├── certs/
│   │   ├── sp.crt
│   │   └── sp.key
│   ├── advanced_settings.json
│   └── settings.json
├── templates/
│   ├── attrs.html
│   ├── base.html
│   └── index.html
├── tests/
│   └── test_saml.py
├── conftest.py
├── requirements.txt
└── run.py
```

